</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,151,1905]" pageId="20" pageNumber="521">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1735,1760]" pageId="20" pageNumber="521">Notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[280,460,1735,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Hydrellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wirthi">
<emphasis box="[280,460,1735,1760]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="521">Hydrellia wirthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded for the first time from 
<collectingCountry box="[849,921,1735,1760]" name="Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="521">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Korytkowski" box="[931,1159,1735,1760]" pageId="20" pageNumber="521" refString="Korytkowski, C. A. (1982) La mosca minadora del arroz en el Peru, Hydrellia wirthi nueva especie. (Diptera: Ephydridae). Revista Peruana del Entomologia, 25 (1), 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1982">
Korytkowski (
<number box="[1092,1150,1736,1760]" pageId="20" pageNumber="521" value="1982.0">1982</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation box="[1213,1436,1735,1760]" pageId="20" pageNumber="521" refString="Mathis, W. N., Castro, B. A., Way, M. O. &amp; Zatwarnicki, T. (2006) Discovery of the South American Rice Miner (Diptera: Ephydridae) in Southeastern United States. Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 99 (6), 999 - 1005. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1603 / 0013 - 8746 (2006) 99 [999: dotsar] 2.0. co; 2" type="journal article">
Mathis 
<emphasis box="[1298,1347,1735,1760]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="521">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[1369,1428,1735,1760]" pageId="20" pageNumber="521" value="2006.0">2006</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
illustrated sternite 
<number box="[363,377,1772,1797]" pageId="20" pageNumber="521" value="5.0">5</number>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[418,520,1772,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Hydrellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wirthi">
<emphasis box="[418,520,1772,1797]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="521">H. wirthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as V-shaped, but in Brazilian specimens it has another shape once it is partially separated from hypandrium, as in figs. 
<number box="[602,651,1808,1832]" pageId="20" pageNumber="521" value="14.1">14.1</number>
and 
<number box="[709,761,1808,1832]" pageId="20" pageNumber="521" value="14.2">14.2</number>
, with the dorsal half similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[1124,1253,1807,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Hydrellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="griseola">
<emphasis box="[1124,1253,1807,1832]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="521">H. griseola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species is morphologically very similar to others from 
<taxonomicName box="[647,739,1844,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Hydrellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="griseola">
<emphasis box="[647,739,1844,1869]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="521">griseola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1070,1141,1844,1869]" name="Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="521">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, mainly 
<taxonomicName box="[1236,1340,1844,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Hydrellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vilelai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1236,1340,1844,1869]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="521">H. vilelai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1347,1436,1844,1869]" pageId="20" pageNumber="521" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1347,1436,1844,1869]" pageId="20" pageNumber="521">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[198,318,1879,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Hydrellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[198,318,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="521">H. simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[325,414,1879,1904]" pageId="20" pageNumber="521">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[325,414,1879,1904]" pageId="20" pageNumber="521" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, being necessary the analyses of male or female terminalia to distinguish them.
</paragraph>
